OL,7,FEnergy watchdog Ofgem has launched an
OL,8,Finvestigation after a report by the
OL,9,FNational Energy System Operator (Neso)
OL,10,Fsaid an "elevated moisture reading"
OL,11,Fhad been found in oil samples at the
OL,12,FNorth Hyde substation in July 2018,
OL,13,Fbut action was not taken to replace
OL,14,Felectrical insulators known as
OL,15,Fbushings.
OL,17,FIn 2022, a decision was made to "defer
OL,18,Fbasic maintenance" at the substation,
OL,19,Fmeaning the issue went "unaddressed",
OL,20,Fthe final report said.
